@page "/about"

<PageTitle>About Me — Portfolio</PageTitle>

<!-- HERO -->
<div class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
        <h1>About Me</h1>
        <p>Beyond the code — who I am, what drives me, and how I spend my time away from the keyboard.</p>
    </div>
</div>

<!-- BIO -->
<div class="section-full">
    <div class="section">
        <div class="grid-2" style="align-items: start;">
            <div>
                <h2 class="section-title"><span class="title-accent">—</span> Who I Am</h2>
                <p style="font-size: 1.05rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;">
                    I was born and raised in a small village in northern France. From a very young age, I was immersed in the world of video games,
                    and this gradually nurtured my passion for computer science. I quickly wanted to work in the video game industry,
                    and I'm very proud to already be able to say that I've done it!
                </p>
                <p style="font-size: 1.05rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;">
                    Even though I play video games much less these days, I still have a passion for tech and I still love solving problems!
                     If you can't find me behind a screen, look for me on the trails or at the gym!
                </p>
            </div>
            <div>
                <div class="card card-yellow">
                    <h3 class="card-title">Quick Facts</h3>
                    <table style="width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin-top: 0.5rem;">
                        <tr style="border-bottom: 2px solid var(--dark-navy);">
                            <td style="padding: 0.5rem 0; font-weight: 700; font-size: 0.85rem; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.5px; width: 40%;">Location</td>
                            <td style="padding: 0.5rem 0;">Ornans, France</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr style="border-bottom: 2px solid var(--dark-navy);">
                            <td style="padding: 0.5rem 0; font-weight: 700; font-size: 0.85rem; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.5px;">Age</td>
                            <td style="padding: 0.5rem 0;">26</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr style="border-bottom: 2px solid var(--dark-navy);">
                            <td style="padding: 0.5rem 0; font-weight: 700; font-size: 0.85rem; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.5px;">Languages</td>
                            <td style="padding: 0.5rem 0;">French (Native), English (C1)</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr style="border-bottom: 2px solid var(--dark-navy);">
                            <td style="padding: 0.5rem 0; font-weight: 700; font-size: 0.85rem; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.5px;">Status</td>
                            <td style="padding: 0.5rem 0;">
                                <span class="tag tag-teal">Open to Work</span>
                            </td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td style="padding: 0.5rem 0; font-weight: 700; font-size: 0.85rem; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.5px;">Availability</td>
                            <td style="padding: 0.5rem 0;">Immediate</td>
                        </tr>
                    </table>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<!-- HOBBIES -->
<div class="section-full section-alt">
    <div class="section">
        <h2 class="section-title"><span class="title-accent">—</span> Hobbies & Interests</h2>
        <div class="grid-3">
            <div class="hobby-card" style="background-color: var(--off-white);">
                <span class="hobby-icon">🎮</span>
                <h3 class="hobby-title">Gaming</h3>
                <p class="card-text">
                    As I said, I still play video games from time to time! With the right equipment, I try a bit of everything, but God of War remains my favorite.
                </p>
            </div>
            <div class="hobby-card card-teal">
                <span class="hobby-icon">📚</span>
                <h3 class="hobby-title">Reading</h3>
                <p class="card-text">
                    I have a well-stocked library, mainly filled with science fiction, fantasy, and comic books. Unfortunately, the books tend to pile up faster than I can read them... whoops!
                </p>
            </div>
            <div class="hobby-card card-yellow">
                <span class="hobby-icon">🏋️‍♂️</span>
                <h3 class="hobby-title">Working out</h3>
                <p class="card-text">
                    "Mens sana in corpore sano" - A healthy mind in a healthy body. There's nothing like giving it your all to lift weights to unwind!
                </p>
            </div>
            <div class="hobby-card" style="background-color: var(--light-blue);">
                <span class="hobby-icon">🗺️</span>
                <h3 class="hobby-title">Travelling</h3>
                <p class="card-text">
                    Discovering new things is incredibly enriching, and to do that, all you have to do is step outside your home!
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<!-- VALUES -->
<div class="section-full">
    <div class="section">
        <h2 class="section-title"><span class="title-accent">—</span> What I Value (at work)</h2>
        <div class="grid-3">
            <div class="card card-red">
                <h3 class="card-title">Continuous Learning</h3>
                <p class="card-text">
                    Stagnation is something that scares me; I always want to learn, whether through my successes or my failures, I always want to improve.
                </p>
            </div>
            <div class="card card-light-blue">
                <h3 class="card-title">Clean code...</h3>
                <p class="card-text">
                    a well-thought-out, elegant solution that benefits everyone, both for development and maintenance
                </p>
            </div>
            <div class="card" style="background-color: var(--gold);">
                <h3 class="card-title">...that works !</h3>
                <p class="card-text">
                    But it has to work! Far too often, we forget that the most important thing in software engineering is that it works!
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

